            "description": "\u2022\tMember of the BELIZE MATH Olympiad committee and therefore responsible for writing/reviewing the questions. During the MATH Olympiad Shows, I was a head judge or LIVE commentator on KREM RADIO or LOVE FM as the Math specialist.\n\u2022\tFor the past 25 years, I have been an external marker/examiner for CXC. The first four years in Jamaica as a SCEC marker, and thereafter as a CAPE examiner (supervisor). Currently, I am the only examiner from Belize marking Pure Mathematics.\n\u2022\tSince 2010, I am occupying the chair of ATLIB Mathematics whose main responsibility is writing and analyzing the results of the annual ATLIB Mathematics examination which is used as the National Entrance requirement to be accepted by a junior college. After the examination, an accurate statistical analysis is produced for the results. \n\u2022\tMember of the Board of Governors for Stann Creek Ecumenical Junior college representing the staff of SCEJC for four years.\n\u2022\tSince 2012, I serve as Center Supervisor for the ATLIB examinations at Stann Creek Ecumenical Junior College.\n\u2022\tIn 2012 I have been selected by the University of Belize to become a member of the External Peer Review committee (3 members) to review the associate degree and bachelor\u2019s degree in mathematics.\n\u2022\tFrom 2017 \u2013 2022 I occupied the chair of the ATLIB SPORTS committee.",
